<doc id="9578" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=9578" title="Germany gives 16.7 million euro loan to Albania to improve its water supply">
<h1>Germany gives 16.7 million euro loan to Albania to improve its water supply</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Germany%20gives%2016.7%20million%20euro%20loan%20to%20Albania%20to%20improve%20its%20water%20supply&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

&lt;a href="w%3AGermany"&gt;Germany&lt;/a&gt; will lend &lt;a href="w%3AAlbania"&gt;Albania&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3Aeuro"&gt;€&lt;/a&gt;16.7 million (&lt;a href="w%3AUSD"&gt;USD&lt;/a&gt;21.5 million) as part of a loan in order to help the country improve its water supply networks in two southeastern towns, &lt;a href="w%3APogradec"&gt;Pogradec&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="w%3AKorca"&gt;Korca&lt;/a&gt;. The deal was signed last Tuesday between the Albanian Finance Ministry and Germany's government-owned KfW Bank.

Germany has been one of the most significant donors to Albania since the fall of Communism. In total, it has contributed more than €326 million to the country's development, while investing €135 million in its water supply and urban canals. 80% of this has been given through grants.

<h2>References</h2>

<ul>
BULLET::::- Associated Press. "&lt;a href="http%3A//www.forbes.com/home/feeds/ap/2005/05/03/ap1995299.html"&gt;Germany Lends $21.5 Million to Albania&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AForbes"&gt;Forbes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, May 5, 2005

</ul>


