<doc id="9602" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=9602" title="New York City Subway's skip-stop 9 service to make its last run May 27">
<h1>New York City Subway's skip-stop 9 service to make its last run May 27</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=New%20York%20City%20Subway%27s%20skip-stop%209%20service%20to%20make%20its%20last%20run%20May%2027&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 
On Friday, May 27, 2005, ♡❤♡&lt;a href="w%3A9%20%28New%20York%20City%20Subway%20service%29"&gt;9&lt;/a&gt;♡❤♡ trains on the &lt;a href="w%3ANew%20York%20City%20Subway"&gt;New York City Subway&lt;/a&gt; will make their final run, ending rush-hour &lt;a href="w%3Askip-stop"&gt;skip-stop&lt;/a&gt; service on the &lt;a href="w%3AIRT%20Broadway-Seventh%20Avenue%20Line"&gt;IRT Broadway-Seventh Avenue Line&lt;/a&gt; north of &lt;a href="w%3A137th%20Street-City%20College%20%28IRT%20Broadway-Seventh%20Avenue%20Line%20station%29"&gt;137th Street-City College&lt;/a&gt;. During &lt;a href="w%3Arush%20hour"&gt;rush hour&lt;/a&gt;s, the ♡❤♡9♡❤♡ is a skip-stop supplement to the ♡❤♡&lt;a href="w%3A1%20%28New%20York%20City%20Subway%20service%29"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;♡❤♡, running the same route but skipping some stops in &lt;a href="w%3AUpper%20Manhattan"&gt;Upper Manhattan&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="w%3Athe%20Bronx"&gt;the Bronx&lt;/a&gt;. At the same time, the ♡❤♡1♡❤♡ skips other stops, which are only served by the ♡❤♡9♡❤♡ at rush hours; some stops are served by all trains. This service pattern results in slightly faster trains, but longer waits for those going to or from skipped stations.

♡❤♡9♡❤♡ service was started on December 12, 1988, at first running during rush hours and middays. In the mid-1990s, midday ♡❤♡9♡❤♡ service was dropped.

The ♡❤♡&lt;a href="w%3AJ-Z%20%28New%20York%20City%20Subway%20service%29"&gt;J-Z&lt;/a&gt;♡❤♡ skip-stop services on the &lt;a href="w%3ABMT%20Jamaica%20Line"&gt;BMT Jamaica Line&lt;/a&gt; will not be affected, as many passengers ride straight through the skip-stop portion, making the faster service more worthwhile.

