<doc id="9648" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=9648" title="Google suffers DNS outage">
<h1>Google suffers DNS outage</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Google%20suffers%20DNS%20outage&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 
Access to &lt;a href="w%3AGoogle"&gt;Google&lt;/a&gt;, including its other projects, was abruptly interrupted late Saturday when a &lt;a href="w%3ADNS"&gt;DNS&lt;/a&gt; outage caused the search engine giant to be unreachable by the domain ♡❤♡Google.com♡❤♡. &lt;a href="http%3A//labs.google.com"&gt;Google Labs&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="http%3A//www.google.com/maps"&gt;Google Maps&lt;/a&gt;, as well as products of Google such as the &lt;a href="w%3AWeblog"&gt;blogging&lt;/a&gt; service &lt;a href="w%3ABlogger"&gt;Blogger&lt;/a&gt; and free photo-album software &lt;a href="w%3APicasa"&gt;Picasa&lt;/a&gt;, were unaffected. Google.com and its &lt;a href="w%3Asubdomain"&gt;subdomains&lt;/a&gt; were once again functioning as of 0100 UTC.

During the brief outage, some browsers were redirected to SoGoSearch. The site http://www.google.com.net has a link to &lt;a href="http%3A//www.mnema.com/"&gt;Gigantics&lt;/a&gt;, and normally redirects to SoGoSearch. This is probably a procedure that specific browsers implement when they cannot find the proper address. Others were also reported to be redirected to &lt;a href="w%3AMicrosoft"&gt;Microsoft&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href="w%3AMSN"&gt;MSN Search&lt;/a&gt;.

Barbobot reports the DNS may have been stolen for a short time.

