<doc id="10133" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=10133" title="Sony unveils Playstation 3">
<h1>Sony unveils Playstation 3</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Sony%20unveils%20Playstation%203&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

On Monday, President and CEO of &lt;a href="w%3ASony"&gt;Sony&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="w%3AKen%20Kutaragi"&gt;Ken Kutaragi&lt;/a&gt; unveiled the next generation of the &lt;a href="w%3APlayStation"&gt;PlayStation&lt;/a&gt; game console. 

The PlayStation 3 console is planned to:
<ul>
BULLET::::- Be based on &lt;a href="w%3AIBM"&gt;IBM's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3ACell%20%28microprocessor%29"&gt;Cell&lt;/a&gt; processor, containing nine separate processing cores, eight of which are to run at 3.2 GHz.
BULLET::::- Contain six &lt;a href="w%3AUSB%202.0"&gt;USB 2.0&lt;/a&gt; ports and be compatible with a maximum of seven controllers through &lt;a href="w%3ABluetooth"&gt;Bluetooth&lt;/a&gt; technology.
BULLET::::- Use Blu-ray technology, with which a single disc can hold as much as 50 gigabytes.
BULLET::::- Be able to play MP3s and display digital photographs.

</ul>
Last week, there was a leak of details regarding &lt;a href="w%3AMicrosoft"&gt;Microsoft&lt;/a&gt;'s next console, the &lt;a href="w%3AXbox%20360"&gt;Xbox 360&lt;/a&gt;. The Xbox 360 contains the same processor as the PlayStation 3, with three cores, also running at 3.2 GHz.

&lt;a href="w%3ANintendo"&gt;Nintendo&lt;/a&gt;, another competitor, is expected to show off the &lt;a href="w%3ANintendo%20Revolution"&gt;Nintendo Revolution&lt;/a&gt; as part of the &lt;a href="w%3AElectronic%20Entertainment%20Expo"&gt;Electronic Entertainment Expo&lt;/a&gt; (E3) next week. 

The PlayStation 3 is planned to be available in white, black, or silver color, in the spring of 2006.

<h2>Controllers</h2>
Bluetooth (up to 7), USB 2.0 (wired), Wi-Fi (PSP), Network (over IP)

